He was like a dream. Like this image you have that feels so real but as soon as you wake up the harder you try to remember the more it slips away. That's what if felt like to be without him. The more she focused on the amazing times she had with him the more he tended to slip away. So she lied to herself. Push her loving memories to the back of her mind in order to keep what was left of him to herself. She knew that deep down she would never have him again and she probably move on and yet something just couldn't let go of the sweet boy of her dreams. That boy that made her laugh without trying and kept her up for days just thinking of his silly hair or goofy laugh. To her he was unlike any other boy in her life, he was majestic.&nbsp;

Their time together was short lived yet felt like a lifetime. Everyday she would wake up just to see him and fall asleep only to keep in a little bit longer. They expressed their emotions for each other in the strangest of ways that many people found quite unorthidox but she didn't care and neither did he. They kissed with passion and hugged with gratitude both just overjoyed to have found someone that cared for them with the deep emotions they had longed for. But as said before their time together was short lived. She angry ways and his shortness of patience finally drove them apart and the joy the girl once knew was gone.&nbsp;And though she never forgot about him and wrote of him daily, he never quite felt the same for her again. The love he once felt for her began to die and she as well began to die with it.&nbsp;

Many have been told of very few dying of a broken heart but she was one of the few. Her heart in actuality didn't die however her spirit did and with her spirit went her desire to live. This poor girl felt as if her world had crumbled beneath her leaving her nowhere to place her feet. So, with the knot of a rope and a single tear, she released her body of her dead spirit leaving behind a note merely stating one thing, "I lived for his love and now I shall die without it."

So it was confirmed that I, Brittany Harrison, have the flu. Yeah great way to start spring break I'm sure however it hasn't been so bad. I've gotten quite a bit done so far and the doc has me on 100 different meds so I should be well by monday or tuesday.&nbsp; Oh and this is a secret so no one tell but......I'm getting my tatoo this summer but SHHHHHH no one is suppose to know any by no one I mean my parents so yeah. But yeah I'm getting my I'm so excited I'm getting it while I'm away so they really wont know when I get it. Oh and my abs yeah they hurt from coughing so I better be losing some weight from all this exercise of coughing and running up and down stairs so sweat off the fever. Yup thats right....i'm sweating off my fevers so I can cut down on the meds I take. Call me Ms. Resourcefull.&nbsp;

I've done some thinking while lying in bed for most of yesterday and I realized that I'm great. Not the I'm great in a "I"m amazing and no one is better than me so take that" type of way. More of a "I"m great because my life doesnt suck as much as I thought and I have so many reason to be happy and so many people I love that I can't help but be great" type of great. I mean I have great friends like Jillian, who for some reason I've become attached to lately....Margo, who again for some reason I havent grown away from since middle school.....Andrew, who is seriously my other half and not in a relationship type of way but in a way that keeps me from doing bad and stupid things.....Carrie, who recently I've become ubber attached to and I pretty love that girl to death....even Ash, who currently I'm not in the best state with but when we are ok we have a great time together and she can be a really good friend when you need her to be.&nbsp; Plus I have an amazing boyfriend who actually cares when I'm sick and still kisses me when I am cause you know thats love right there. Despite our off and on fighing I really think this last big fight we had might have been the one to put us on track and I really can't see myself with anyone other than him and there is no one I would rather be with&nbsp;plus according to my doctor he is my medicine so I have to keep him around.&nbsp;

So yeah I guess being sick is truly the only time I"m in a condition to really stop and look at everything around me and realize I'm&nbsp; great. Great friends, Great boyfriend, Good Family what else to you truly need?

What do you think? Seriously I want all your honest opinions either about this entry or about me or whatever. Just tell me what you think. I promise to respond.
